00:10:02.440 --> 00:10:04.120
That we need to keep talking about this.

00:10:04.120 --> 00:10:04.360
Yes.

00:10:05.160 --> 00:10:05.320
Yeah.

00:10:05.320 --> 00:10:06.280
That's not old hat.

00:10:06.280 --> 00:10:06.520
No.

00:10:07.400 --> 00:10:08.360
Oh, I'm an artist.

00:10:08.360 --> 00:10:11.160
I'm a contemporary artist, which means that I do all kinds of stuff,

00:10:11.160 --> 00:10:12.520
which are really hard to pigeonhole.

00:10:12.520 --> 00:10:16.680
But basically my work as an artist tends to involve engagement with other people,

00:10:16.680 --> 00:10:21.640
conversations, work involving video or kind of event based stuff.

00:10:21.640 --> 00:10:25.000
I also curate, which means I work with other artists and their practices

00:10:25.000 --> 00:10:27.160
to make events happen so they bring all their artwork in.

00:10:28.040 --> 00:10:30.760
I'm writing as well and I'm writing a book at the moment.

00:10:32.040 --> 00:10:35.640
The main thing, which really was odd about doing the sculptural thing,

00:10:35.720 --> 00:10:39.320
is that I've just started a project for three years called Perfect Me,

00:10:39.320 --> 00:10:43.080
which isn't feminist per se, but it absolutely hits all of those things,

00:10:43.080 --> 00:10:44.920
those things, those kind of targets,

00:10:44.920 --> 00:10:47.800
because it's about our relationship to our bodies, our physicality.

00:10:47.800 --> 00:10:51.320
So I have a big problem, like most women, accepting my body,

00:10:51.320 --> 00:10:56.600
feeling overweight and generally being burdened by the Western objectification of selfhood.

00:10:57.240 --> 00:11:01.320
So yeah, it felt very, very, again, synchronous that we were doing it.

00:11:01.320 --> 00:11:02.600
But also you're bald.

00:11:02.600 --> 00:11:03.640
And also I'm bald.

00:11:03.720 --> 00:11:05.720
So not that big of a deal.

00:11:05.720 --> 00:11:07.800
I'm a pre-Columbian for tinnitus.

